race.comment: GOOD'N'YOU (3) Graff gelding from Don't Doubt Lara on debut for the Ryan & Alexiou stable. Has shown ability in all three trials and finds a winnable race from the good gate. WILLINGHAM (7) returned for his second campaign with a respectable fourth over 1200m at Nowra. Covered plenty of ground from the sticky draw on that occasion and can improve quickly today. CALIFORNIA COMMAND (5) eight-start Maiden resuming after finishing in the minor money on a couple of occasions last prep on the provincial circuit. Given the two trials heading into this and can sit off the solid tempo and close late. BOLLENTE BOY (1) Too Darn Hot gelding out of Prosecco on debut for the O'Shea & Charlton stable. Given three recent trials heading into this and look for him attacking the line over the final 200m.
